e to exercise that interface branch. However, it seems the class$ call only executes if `class$javax$...` is null, meaning if it has a non-null static field from any prior calls, that won't be covered. To address coverage, I could create a fresh copy of the library class through a custom classloader, but that's quite complex. Using Java serialization doesn't seem to be the right fit either.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting dynamic access coverage**\\n\\nI need to look into the TCK runner and see if it can provide dynamic access coverage through the JaCoCo report using the call tree stack. If a class is loaded by a custom loader with the same name, that might count. However, native images can't load new classes from a JAR. I wonder if I could include local native-image metadata to enforce runtime initialization or register `SimpleTagSupport` for that purpose. I might need to add test resources with `--initialize-at-run-time=javax.servlet.jsp.tagext.SimpleTagSupport`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_bpo6feANVEKWJg6Bi4BX6iN9|fc_0ce04a3ba3fd22ec0169f5491a4a4081a0bf4f8381325eb56c", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javax.servlet/jsp-api/2.0/src/test/java/javax_servlet/jsp_api/SimpleTagSupportTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void findsSimpleTagAncestorByConcreteClass() {\n        SimpleTagSupport ancestor = new SimpleTagSupport();\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\n        child.setParent(ancestor);\n\n        JspTag found = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, SimpleTagSupport.class);\n\n        assertThat(found).isSameAs(ancestor);\n    }\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void findsAncestorAfterLoadingTheJspTagContract() {\n        SimpleTagSupport ancestor = new SimpleTagSupport();\n        SimpleTagSupport child = new SimpleTagSupport();\n        child.setParent(ancestor);\n\n        JspTag found = SimpleTagSupport.findAncestorWithClass(child, JspTag.class);\n\n        assertTh