’m thinking that \\\"dynamic-access coverage\\\" might relate to agent metadata rather than the line itself. To adequately cover the Class.forName call site, the agent would need to record `Class.forName` as dynamic access. If the class is already statically reachable, maybe the agent doesn't need to do that? I should probably check the documentation and look for more information on dynamic access to clarify things.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Tyl1NjWpBpj1RKSDz4mf2suB|fc_0ce04a3ba3fd22ec0169f549bcb5dc81a096d8473928faa57b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"dynamic-access\" -n build.gradle tests/src docs forge | head -50"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1443, "output": 612, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24071, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777682865840, "responseId": "resp_0ce04a3ba3fd22ec0169f549b24f8c81a0b00533a80beb383e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Tyl1NjWpBpj1RKSDz4mf2suB|fc_0ce04a3ba3fd22ec0169f549bcb5dc81a096d8473928faa57b", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:329:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1768:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1798:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1809:        \"dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1810:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1815:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1942:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1946:        \"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1965:        f\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1967:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1969:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2631:            pipeline_argv.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4537:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4540:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4541:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\nforge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:75:    \"\"\"Return True when the dynamic-access stats entry matches the expected object shape.\"\"\"\nforge/utility_scripts/dynamic_access_report.py:160:        return \"All dynamic-access call sites are covered.\"\nforge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:35:            \"[dynamic-access] ===================================================================================\\n\"\nforge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:36:            \"[dynamic-access] Progress after org.example.SomeClass: \"\nforge/tests/test_dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:38:            \"[dynamic-access] ===================================================================================\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies