ing. \\n\\nInstead, maybe I should update the test to assert the result of a helper via both `JspTag.class` and another class, keeping comments concise.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering ancestor retrieval via SimpleTagSupport**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using `SimpleTagSupport.class` to return the ancestor through class assignability. It seems like the initial attempt was already aimed at that. I wonder if refining this approach could lead to the desired outcome. I need to ensure that I'm considering all possible angles for correctly accessing the ancestor. There's a chance this might work, and I just need to clarify my implementation to avoid any issues. I'll keep exploring this!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test implementation**\\n\\nI want to work with subclass inheritance and a public nested interface without a package for better API coverage. There’s a question about whether to delete a placeholder, especially if it conflicts with a dynamic class and generated test files. I think it's essential to ensure the tests invoke necessary methods while reviewing the test report to ensure previous external changes were covered. I’m considering refining the testing strategy with `@TestMethodOrder` and looking into static initialization options too.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting TagAdapter**\\n\\nI need to focus on creating a TagAdapter constructor. It seems if the parent is a TagAdapter, the method unwraps, but I’m curious about inspecting what TagAdapter requires in terms of SimpleTag. I’m thinking focusing on the active class might work out fine, so it’s a matter of balancing this alongside ensuring everything integrates smoothly. I'm pondering if there are any additional requirements or adjustments needed for the adaptation process.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_VcfOBc5GfZuvPKLYANw6RJYs|fc_0ce04a3ba3fd22ec0169f54a26944481a090017779b2f77404", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "javap